Joe Cattini marked the milestone with a party at his retirement complex at Fair Oak in Hampshire – and was made an honorary citizen of Eindhoven in the Netherlands by its delegation. The former bombardier in the 86th (Hertfordshire Yeomanry) Field Regiment, Royal Artillery landed on Normandy’s Gold Beach on June 6 1944. His best pal was killed next to him in the invasion of Germany near the end of the Second World War. Joe recalled: “When you are young, you think war is a game. Something you can laugh about. War is very serious. It affects everybody.”